<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-illegiblelineapprox" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Illegible Lines, Quantity Approximate (Circa or Range)</head>
    <p><!--gloss--></p>
    <p><specList>
            <specDesc key="gap"/>
        </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p>

    <p>Where vestiges of lines remain, but they cannot be recognised and their quantity is
        approximate, they should be placed in a <gi>gap</gi> element and given a <att>reason</att>
        attribute with a value of "illegible", and either an attribute of <att>precision</att> with
        the value "low" (to express 'circa'), or a range of possible lines lost using the
        attributes <att>atLeast</att> and <att>atMost</att>.</p>

    <cit>
        <quote>[- - - - - -]</quote>
        <bibl corresp="#panciera"> <!-- VIII.5 is a normal gap (lines lost) - there is no Panciera section corresponding exactly to 'Illegible Lines, Quantity Approximate' but I think this would be rendered the same way -->
            <biblScope>VIII.5</biblScope>
        </bibl>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="line" precision="low"/>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera">
        <gap reason="illegible" atLeast="3" atMost="5" unit="line"/>
    </egXML>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/???"> <!-- Can't find o.heid.490 online -->
        <gap reason="illegible" quantity="4" unit="line" precision="low"><desc>vestiges</desc></gap>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/bgu;3;916">
        <gap reason="illegible" atLeast="2" atMost="3" unit="line"><desc>vestiges</desc></gap>
    </egXML>
    
<!-- No IRT or iAph examples -->
    
